            <p>WVO heating, decanting, and filtration are costly and labor-intensive, especially for large-scale processing of WVO and similar used oils.</p>
            <p>Industrial centrifuges are ideal for continuously separating water and sludge from WVO. WVO could be in the form of grease trap waste, yellow grease, used cooking oil, etc. <a href="/disc-stack-centrifuge/">Alfa Laval disc stack centrifuges</a> are often used for separating solids and water from WVO. These fully-automatic machines are set up for flow-through separation of water and sludge from WVO.</p>
            <p>The Alfa Laval self-cleaning 3-phase centrifuge system shown processes WVO at 3–5 GPM at 180&deg;F. Read our blog about <a href="/yellow-grease-purification-centrifuge/">large-scale WVO processing with an industrial centrifuge</a>.</p>
