          <h3 class="font-heading text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold text-navy mb-3">
            <a href="/algae-centrifuge/" class="hover:text-gold-dark transition-colors">Algae Harvesting Centrifuge</a>
          </h3>
          <div class="prose-dolphin text-[15px] text-text-light leading-relaxed space-y-3">
            <p>Algae is the new biofuel of interest. Algae cell harvesting requires processing a large volume of water to concentrate small amounts of algae cells. Algae cells are microscopic, and their specific gravity is close to the medium (water). This is a challenging application for any separation process, especially those using media such as filters or presses.</p>
            <p>Alfa Laval centrifuges are efficient at commercial-scale harvesting and algae separation. Disc stack centrifuges generate upwards of <strong>7,000 Gs</strong> of centrifugal force in the bowl — enough to separate the algae cells from water. Large-capacity centrifugal separators harvest algae at up to <strong>150 GPM</strong> on a commercial scale. Typically these are <a href="/stainless-steel-centrifuge/">stainless steel centrifuges</a> with all wetted parts made of 316L stainless steel.</p>
            <p>Dolphin Centrifuge supplied <a href="/algae-centrifuge/">Alfa Laval disc stack centrifuges for algae harvesting</a> at a fisheries plant in Thailand. The concentrated algae cells are nutritious fish larvae feed.</p>
