          <h3 class="font-heading text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold text-navy mb-3">
            <a href="/biodiesel-centrifuge/" class="hover:text-gold-dark transition-colors">Biodiesel Glycerin Separation Centrifuge</a>
          </h3>
          <div class="prose-dolphin text-[15px] text-text-light leading-relaxed space-y-3">
            <p>The chemical reaction of vegetable oil with lye or other caustic agent and alcohol produces biodiesel. This process produces biodiesel and glycerol (glycerin mixed with alcohol). The dense phase (glycerol) separates from the lighter biodiesel under gravity. Draining this dense phase produces crude biodiesel.</p>
            <p>This gravity settling is a time-consuming process that also requires extra storage capacity. Also, it does not produce pure biodiesel. Alfa Laval centrifuges are a fast and cost-effective way to separate the glycerin from biodiesel.</p>
            <p>Dolphin-modified Alfa Laval centrifuges produce ASTM-spec biodiesel without the need for further processing. The system shown is a Teflon-coated <a href="/biodiesel-centrifuge/">biodiesel centrifuge</a> system manufactured for a domestic biodiesel producer. The use of methanol requires special modifications including VITON elastomers in wetted areas and C1 D2 electrical components.</p>
