            <a href="/crude-oil-tank-bottom-recovery-centrifuge/" class="hover:text-gold-dark transition-colors">Crude Oil Tank Bottom Recovery Centrifuge</a>
          </h3>
          <div class="prose-dolphin text-[15px] text-text-light leading-relaxed space-y-3">
            <p>Crude oil from the ground carries salt water, sand, or other sludge. Producers use settling tanks to separate crude oil from Bottom Sediment &amp; Water, also known as BS&amp;W. Tank bottoms are the residue left in the settling tanks after the removal of sale oil. Recovery of this oil is extra revenue for the producer.</p>
            <p>An Alfa Laval <a href="/industrial-centrifuge/">industrial centrifuge</a> is a cost-effective solution for tank bottom processing to recover sale oil. It uses centrifugal force to separate the tank bottom sludge from the oil. The 3-phase centrifuge also separates water from the oil, delivering clean crude oil with <strong>less than 0.5% BS&amp;W</strong>.</p>
            <p>Dolphin Centrifuge has designed an engineered solution for efficient, low-cost crude oil recovery. Our containerized Oil Recovery System is a self-contained packaged module for remote field applications, recovering sale oil with <strong>less than 0.1% BS&amp;W</strong>. <a href="/crude-oil-centrifuge/">Crude oil centrifuges</a> are also used at Salt Water Disposals for produced water separation.</p>
